CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1772485564
OL,3,CBritish philanthropist Sir David Kirch
OL,4,Cdies aged 89
OL,6,FOnce he was diagnosed with cancer, he
OL,7,Fpledged his entire fortune to
OL,8,Fpensioners - reportedly having already
OL,9,Fgiven away more than #100 million.
OL,11,FReacting to his passing, Jersey's
OL,12,FChief Minister, Deputy Lyndon Farnham,
OL,13,Fsays: "Sir David was a truly
OL,14,Fremarkable man who used his wealth to
OL,15,Fbetter the lives of so many,
OL,16,Fparticularly the elderly.
OL,18,F"He loved island life and saw it as a
OL,19,Fgreat privilege to live here, and
OL,20,Fbecause of this, he made it his
OL,21,Fmission to give back to the community.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/4
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1772485564
OL,3,CBritish philanthropist Sir David Kirch
OL,4,Cdies aged 89
OL,6,F"There are few others who have done so
OL,7,Fmuch for elderly islanders in Jersey.
OL,8,FThe island has lost one of its greats,
OL,9,Fbut his name will live on in the work
OL,10,Fof his charitable trust."
OL,12,FThe Housing Minister, Deputy Sam
OL,13,FMezec, adds: "Sir David is rightly
OL,14,Fheld in deep affection by so many
OL,15,Fislanders, especially pensioners, for
OL,16,Fhis huge generosity towards the
OL,17,Felderly in Jersey.
OL,26,@uD@Brr
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/4
